What we have sent you is all that we make. You see our Blanc de Blancs is a very special Champagne. It is made only from the white Pinot Chardonnay grape which grows on only one hillside in all of France.

And if in some years the grapes are not good enough, we do not make the champagne at all. That is why there will be no 1963 and no 1965 Blanc de Blancs to carry the Ruinart name. We take pride in our name. We are a family business, the oldest champagne firm in France.
